If initializeLocalObjectFlags() is executed for non-realTimeGC too, then we have a problem today because the following code:
   if (!TR::Options::getCmdLineOptions()->realTimeGC())
      {
      initValue |= vmThread()->allocateThreadLocalHeap.objectFlags;
      }

accesses vmThread()->allocateThreadLocalHeap.objectFlags  for non-realTImeGC case.
On the other hand, if initializeLocalObjectFlags() is only entered for realTimeGC, then that if statement shown above is never taken.

